      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">Scientific Governance</div>
        <h2 class="h2 reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:24px;max-width:14ch">Designed to know where interpretation must stop.</h2>
        <p class="lead reveal" data-d="2" style="margin-top:28px">The hardest part of developmental intelligence is restraint. PLINTH HDI is governed by principles that decide, continuously, how far interpretation is allowed to go.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gov__lines reveal" data-d="1">
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Confidence-aware reasoning</h4><p>The system weighs how much it knows before it says anything at all.</p></div>
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Non-diagnostic philosophy</h4><p>PLINTH HDI never assigns clinical or fixed categories to a developing child.</p></div>
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Contextual interpretation</h4><p>Every signal is read inside its environment — context before trait.</p></div>
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Human oversight</h4><p>People remain accountable for what is interpreted and how it is shared.</p></div>
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Openness preservation</h4><p>Interpretations stay revisable — a child is never closed into a conclusion.</p></div>
        <div class="gov__line"><h4>Anti-coherence safeguards</h4><p>Guards against over-tidy narratives that feel certain but aren't earned.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

